storyText: Tap Select Recommended!
It'll pick your gear for you!
Classes have abilities but also restrictions.
Be aware that each class can
equip different weapons.
Call upon nightmares you've captured in battle.
They're super strong, so set them to work.
Time to forfeit those shimmering rocks you so desire: twilight crystals.
And in return...
You get treasures we've collected from different stories.
Now to teach you how to upgrade!
Start with a weapon with a high rarity as your base.
Feed it any materials you don't need!
Skill level is the most important. So aim to raise
the skill level of your favorite weapons to Lv. 5!
It's really easy! Even a mangy mutt could do it!
We'll unlock a new feature for you!
Don't miss those limited-time events!
We'll unlock a new feature for you!
Help out your comrades and win their admiration!
You'll get special medals for fighting with
your friends in co-op battles!
Collect medals and trade them for limited classes and more!
Here you can equip weapons in your sub-set.
You can't use skills from weapons set as sub gear,
but your stats will get a little boost.
You can expand your sub-set as your rank increases.
Lastly, a word of caution...
You can't equip the same weapon in both main and sub-sets.
If you can't choose, just tap Select Recommended!
Look at how strong you've become.
Now get out there and start gatherin' lifeforce.
Join a guild and participate in the Colosseum!
You'll get rewards just by joining a guild.
Enter a guild with lots of people so you can mooch off 'em!
Congrats on joining a guild!
You're now invited to a true death match: the Colosseum!
Great work!
But you're just gettin' started!
You gotta keep on winning.
The Colosseum is hard, but the rewards are worth it.
Colosseum rewards will make you even stronger.
You can get super strong classes!
You can also get weapons dear to the authors!
But first, you gotta keep fighting in the Colosseum.
We'll show you how to equip stuff!
Different classes have different
gear they can and can't use.
We'll hide weapons you can't equip.
But it's not like we're stealin' them from you,
so relax! Tsk.
Congrats! You've unlocked the Act of Reality!
Now you'll finally find out the sins your characters hide...
And to match the tone, we've changed the background music.
If you prefer the previous background music, change it
by going to Menu > Options > Music.
Take it easy!
The story of April Fools dates back to
France's adoption of the Gregorian calendar.
France used to ring in the new year on April 1.
But in the year 1564, King Charles IX
Decided to switch to January 1, per the Gregorian system.
Naturally, the citizens handling the festivities were livid.
They fought back by celebrating a false new year on April 1.
That foolish ballyhoo was passed down continuously
and became the April Fools we know today.
Do you feel like you get it now?
But April Fools falls on April 1.
That's an April fool.

April Loops?

France's adoption of the Gregorian calendar.
France used to ring in the new year on April 1.
But in the year 1564, King Charles IX
Decided to switch to January 1, per the Gregorian system.
Naturally, the citizens handling the festivities were livid.
They fought back by celebrating a false new year on April 1.
That foolish ballyhoo was passed down continuously
and became the April Fools we know today.
Wait a moment. Do you feel a hint of déjà vu?
Could it be all that about getting crystals…
...was an April fools joke?
Who should our next collaboration be with?
We could go for, you know, that one game...
But to attract a whole new audience,
we want to seek out all kinds of surprise collaborations!
There's been a lot more lately.
Like of a man-free world…
It really pulls my strings!
I'm sure you want to know why!
Did men just vanish right out of the world?
Or did something cause the male population to dwindle?
I demand answers!
But you can't go forgetting what day April 1 is!
That's an April fool.
Dear reader, did you know?
There's a certain rumor surrounding April Fools...
That is...
"The lies we tell on April Fools don't come true."
That's the idea!
So if those lies are imbued with even the faintest of hopes...
If they're told on April 1,
they won't come true.
Isn't that ironic?
If your hopes for a collaboration are false, they won't be true either.
But this could all turn out to be idle gossip.
After all, April 1...
Well, that's April Fools Day!
The story of April Fools dates back to
France's adoption of the Gregorian calendar.
France used to ring in the new year on April 1.
But in the year 1564, King Charles IX
Decided to switch to January 1, per the Gregorian system.
Naturally, the citizens handling the festivities were livid.
They fought back by celebrating a false new year on April 1.
That foolish ballyhoo was passed down continuously
and became the April Fools we know today.
Wait a second, is this looping?
Could it be all that about getting crystals…
April Loops?
On April Fools Day, you can get away with lying.
A special day indeed.
But that doesn't mean you can only tell lies.
Sometimes you tell the truth.
So the part about getting crystals is true!
You helped us out with this headache of a picture-hunt.
Thank you very much!
Have a present of 100 crystals!
Thank you for trusting us!
Thank you so much, for now and every time!
We hope you get every bit of enjoyment you can.
We'll keep giving it our all!
Oh, and that's not a lie!
Absolutely true!
Look how many points you've accumulated!
At last, it's time to unlock a new power!
You can take up to three of these powers into the Colosseum!
But you can only change while reloading your weapon!
Now, take this power and go gather lots of lifeforce!
Hello hello!
We heard plenty of you saying, "I don't get what to do!"\n So here we are to give some advice.
Well, not that it's a particularly confusing game anyway.
In short: play the story, collect crystals, summon from the grimoire\n and upgrade your weapons.
We've added a feature in the top left called Rookies' Path,\n so give it a tap if you're lost!
In general, tap the arrow button to complete the tasks.
Clear the entire guide and you'll get an Alice/Mage!
Go dive on in!
Is your gear list just about full?
Is your present box just about to burst?
Well, good news!
Inventory management is now unlocked!
It'll help clear out that mountain of a present box!
And no more not being able to find your gear in the list!
Gather it all up for a nice, satisfying purge!
Perfect for you stuff-it-in-the-drawer types!
Put it in storage and it won't up and disappear!
No need to worry about time limits for claiming!
Why not clean out your present box?
Until next time!
All goes bye-bye!
Good news for all you limit breakers!\nYou can unlock new abilities by limit breaking!
Mind telling us what that is?
Listen and be amazed! For it's called a limit break skill!
...That's it?
Lame. They didn't even try to be creative.
Well, tell us how it works.
Right now we have story, Colosseum, and Colosseum support skills. But this new addition makes four!
It'll boost your stats and buff you up at the beginning of battle. At least, that's the plan.
The heck's that supposed to mean?
Some of the effects are still in development.
...That's not surprising. I'll keep my hopes up.
And? So how do they work?
All you gotta do is limit break an SR with the skill to unlock it.
Then, set that weapon in your deck's "slot" to activate the effect.
"Slot"?
Yeah. Well, it's not available yet, but it will be! Give it some time.
Aren't you getting ahead of yourself?
Anyway, just start preparing! Limit break your weapons!
What he said.
...Kehehehe.
This will make gathering desires more efficient.
I think they heard you, Noya.
Did they? My bad.
If you're still confused, check out the help page.
An announcement for all those who've raised their colosseum records.
The time for Colosseum Sin has finally come.
Colosseum Sin is a special colosseum event
where only high ranking guilds with brilliant records
can join in the Gran Colosseum.
Colosseum Sin is separated into two divisions.
For the high ranked guilds,
they are separated into higher rank and lower ranks.
The higher rank division is called the Ultimate 32
Only the top 32 guilds will be advanced.
Those who advance into the Ultimate 32,
can get division-exclusive stamps and titles.
In other words...bragging rights.
If you want to boast endlessly—and you certainly do...
Welcome to Upgrade Character!
Looks like we've got another weird new feature. Where do we ever start with this? Anyway, we'll do our best to give you a quick run down and be on our way.
Upgrade Character is a place where you can use specific items to strengthen your characters as you see fit.
Another half-hearted title.
What else did you expect from them?
Next up is the Character Board. There's one for each of our Library characters.
The orbs on this board give you really cool things when you use items on them.
Mind explaining what those cool things are?
Like boosting parameters, increasing costs, and adding more slots for limit break skills.
So basically an advantage in battle.
Exactly that. All stuff that'll help you in battle.
And where can I get these items to unlock them?
You can earn them at the Colosseum.
Sounds simple enough. I'll get started right away.
Hold your horses. I'm not done explaining things.
Can you try to make it quick? I don't got all day.
See, there's actually four different routes on the board. Depending on which one you choose, you'll unlock different abilities.
You can choose from Balance, Physical Upgrade, Magic Upgrade, and Mega Upgrade.
You're making me choose? Just tell me your recommendation.
Sure, take the Balance route first until you get used to the system.
There's a lot to learn. It would be useful if there was something I could turn to for help.
That's already covered! Everything's been added to the manual, so you'll find your way around.
Have fun customizing your characters!
What's the matter?
What's this Unlockable Soul Seals thing?
Oh, that? There's a limit to how many soul seals can be unlocked for each character.
You never mentioned that!
I'm calling management.
...Hello? This is Parrah.
Woah, take it easy. There's methods to increase the limit!
I'm listening.
If you wanna increase the availability, all ya gotta do is acquire more classes or use the almighty item Zenith Bookmark.
I see. So the more classes I have, the more soul seals I can unlock.
Yeah! Easy to follow, right?
If you're still confused, check the How to Play manual.
Can't wait to see how much stronger you'll get!
Looks like you've got a character with an outfit change,\nor a special sort of player character.
one that lets you give your player character a makeover\nas long as you've got the class for it sitting around somewhere.
It's been a long time coming, huh?
Still, I see that look of wild confusion in your eyes.\nYou're not sure about the rules, are you?
Well, worry not!
Just go to the Choose Player Character screen,
and tap and hold the icon.\nYou'll be able to check all sorts of fiddly details if you do that.
Hm? You want to know what'll happen to the character's status?
Well, it'll be the same as\ntheir base class, of course.
Oh, dear, I see all these four-dollar words are confusing you.\nYou want to know what a base class is?
Well, it's the original class the character's got.\nYou know, the one with all the skills and status stuff you actually want to use?
In other words, you can change how\nthe character looks
while still holding onto, say, the \nskills and status of a Half-Nightmare. Neat, huh?
Exactly!
So go ahead, get yourself out of that boring rut!\nYou'll be a totally new you, with your fresh new style!
Head right on over to the Edit Gear screen, and...
What.\nYou STILL have questions?
Gotcha.
You want to know the deal with the masks icon?
Well, if this baby shows up,\nthen you'll know you've changed the character's appearance.
To be even more precise,\nonce you DO change how your character looks,
their class icon is going to stay the same,\nstill showing the base class
on the Colosseum Members List
and right there next to their name
the masks icon will appear so you'll be able to check\nwhat their original class actually is.
Change a character's look for the Main Set,\nand the change will carry through
to purification and the Profile,\nso head on over to the Edit Gear screen to try it out!
Are you bored of your guildship's design?
Then do we got good news for you!
Now there's a feature to customize the appearance of your guildship.
We call it, "Guildship Revamp".
With this, you can metamorphosize
your guildship any way you like!
Soar on a ship with aesthetics.\nThat's what you really want.
But first you gotta get "parts"
for your ship.
You can change your guildship's looks by
replacing your current parts with the new ones.
Not only will you fly in style, but
your ship will also get an HP boost!
The more parts you acquire, the less
likely you'll be shot down at the Colosseum.
You can purchase parts using guildship points,
which you can earn as rewards at the Colosseum.
And when you do make a kick-ass lookin'
guildship ready to steal all that lifeforce,
show it off to other guilds by posting it online.
We're gonna unlock a new feature for you,
one that lets you give your player character a makeover\nas long as you've got the class for it sitting around somewhere.
At long last!
Break free and truly express your inner self by changing your character's appearance!
Yaaay!!
Yaaaaaaaaaaay!!
Ahem. Any questions?
What is it?
You want to know if there are any limits\non this so-called free expression?
Well, obviously. You've gotta have the job for it, first of all.\nAnd even then,
the class you choose for your new look\nneeds to have the same specialty weapon type as the base class.
Otherwise, no glow up for you!
So, if you're trying to style up a Breaker,\nyou'll need to choose another Breaker
as for your new look.
Simple, right?
Oh! Almost forgot!
Some special player characters\nhave some special conditions if you want to change their appearance.
If you're having trouble finding the player character\nyou've had your eye on,
try using the Filter feature to make things a little easier.
strive for the lifeforce and aim for the top.
Check the notices for more details.
Looks like you've reached 80,000 points.
Congrats! You've just unlocked Support Classes!
Support classes? The heck are those?
Simply put, now you can equip classes.
Equip a class to a class?\nWhat's the point of that?
Each class you equip adds an extra 100 HP to your base.
...Huh?\nYou're joking, right? That's completely useless!
Of course there's more! Shut up and listen.
First you gotta unlock support skills.\nAfter that, equip your class and…
You'll activate that class's support skill!
Gotcha.
It's tough keeping up with all these new terms though.
Just check your class's details to see what kind of effect it\n activates.
You can't just leave us at a cliffhanger! Tell us more!
Support skills are a class skill that come with some class series'.
Or you can use arcana to unlock it on some others.
But you gotta equip it to use it. That's when the real magic happens.
Oh, and I guess I should mention…
Earning more points will unlock\nmore slots to equip support classes.
But you need to get even stronger to do that.
Put it to use and magnify your lifeforce count!
So, we released a photo op feature.
It's limited to this event,
so we need the players to bring their own cameras.
Let's get into the details then, shall we?
First, select a stamp from the list on the edit screen.
All you gotta do is tap it.
Then you can adjust the size, angle, and position. Make it just the way you like.
If you have more than one stacked, you can choose which goes on top.
And if you decide not to use a stamp you selected, you can toss it in the trash.
When you're satisfied with your edits, press the
shutter button at the bottom of the screen.
Your finished photo will display afterwards. If you like it, save it as a screenshot!
Tap on the photo to finish your photo session.
So get on snappin'! We expect some good shots from you!
Mmh...?
Looks like we've come to a split in the road.
That's right!
One path takes you to the continuation of the main scenario.
Gotcha.
The other path leads to a sub quest.
There you can view some extra stuff not shown in the other.
Makes sense!
You don't actually HAVE to do the sub quests. Just focus on the main story if that's all you care about.
But they're here if you ever wanna come back.
Kee-hee-hee.
Heehee…
The moment is finally here.
The first volley has been fired in the battle to decide who'll take the top spot.
Right now, at the Polls,
you can choose from First Place Guild Predictions
and Final Battle Prediction.
Use Twilight Crystals/WGC to cast your ballots.
First Place Guild Predictions can be made up until the start of the Top 16.
Final Battle Predictions can be made from the day the match-up is released until the day before the battle.
Don't forget to vote!
You won't want to take your eyes off
the battle to decide the number one guild!
Good work!
It's harvest season!
Thanks to the spirits, we brought in a hefty harvest!
We'll harvest together!
Reap the rest of 'em through purification!
You're needed in this venture.
Kehehe...
Nice harvest!
You really helped up bring in the loads!
It's just a small thing, but
we sent yer reward to your home screen.
Use it on something good to eat.
And don't forget to harvest when you've got the time!
There's still plenty of crops out there.
